-- Sample Vacancy Data

INSERT INTO vacancies (title, short_description, description, location, salary, type, category, responsibilities, qualifications, skills, start_date, end_date) 
VALUES  ('Administrative Assistant','Coordinate daily office operations and provide comprehensive administrative support to department heads. Manage correspondence and schedules.','As an Administrative Assistant at Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for providing comprehensive administrative support to department heads and ensuring smooth daily operations across all departments. Your role will involve managing correspondence, coordinating meetings and appointments, maintaining organized filing systems, and serving as the primary point of contact for internal and external stakeholders. You will work closely with senior officials to prepare reports, presentations, and official documents while ensuring compliance with government protocols and procedures. This position requires exceptional organizational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to handle multiple priorities in a fast-paced government environment. You will also be responsible for managing office supplies, coordinating logistics for meetings and events, and maintaining confidentiality of sensitive government information.','Lideta Subcity Office',42000,'fulltime','Administration','{"Manage and coordinate calendars, appointments, and meetings for department heads, ensuring optimal scheduling and time management across multiple priorities while anticipating conflicts and proposing solutions","Prepare, proofread, and format official documents, reports, presentations, and correspondence according to government standards and protocols, ensuring accuracy, consistency, and professional presentation","Maintain comprehensive electronic and physical filing systems for administrative documents, correspondence, and records, implementing efficient retrieval systems and ensuring compliance with government record-keeping regulations","Serve as primary liaison between department heads and other government offices, community organizations, and the public, handling inquiries professionally and directing them to appropriate personnel","Coordinate logistics for meetings, conferences, and official events including venue arrangements, equipment setup, catering, and preparation of meeting materials and agendas","Manage office supplies inventory, procurement processes, and equipment maintenance, anticipating needs and ensuring continuous availability of essential resources","Process and track official correspondence, memos, and communications, ensuring timely distribution and proper documentation of all official communications","Assist in budget preparation and monitoring by tracking expenditures, processing invoices, and maintaining financial records for departmental operations"}','{"Minimum of Diploma in Office Management, Business Administration, or related field from an accredited institution with demonstrated coursework in administrative procedures and office technology","At least two years of progressive administrative support experience in government offices, corporate environments, or large organizations with proven ability to handle sensitive information confidentially","Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) and government document management systems with ability to create complex documents, spreadsheets, and presentations","Exceptional written and verbal communication skills in Amharic and English with demonstrated ability to draft professional correspondence and communicate effectively with diverse stakeholders","Proven organizational and time management abilities with capacity to prioritize multiple tasks, meet deadlines, and maintain attention to detail in high-pressure situations","Strong interpersonal skills with ability to build positive working relationships with officials, colleagues, and community members while maintaining professional boundaries","Knowledge of government administrative procedures, document handling protocols, and official communication channels within Ethiopian government structure","Ability to maintain confidentiality of sensitive information and exercise discretion in handling official matters and interpersonal communications"}','{"document_management","time_management","communication_skills"}','2024-01-15','2024-02-15'),
        ('Public Health Officer','Lead community health initiatives and disease prevention programs. Conduct epidemiological surveillance and coordinate health education campaigns.','As a Public Health Officer for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will play a critical role in protecting and improving community health through comprehensive public health initiatives, disease surveillance, and health education programs. Your responsibilities will encompass monitoring population health trends, investigating disease outbreaks, implementing preventive health measures, and coordinating with healthcare facilities and community organizations. You will develop and execute public health campaigns addressing prevalent health issues in the Lideta community, including infectious diseases, maternal and child health, nutrition, and non-communicable diseases. This position requires extensive fieldwork, data analysis, and community engagement to identify health disparities and implement targeted interventions. You will serve as a technical advisor on public health matters, providing evidence-based recommendations to government officials and collaborating with regional health authorities to align subcity initiatives with national health priorities and Sustainable Development Goals.','Lideta Health Center',58000,'fulltime','Health','{"Design, implement, and evaluate comprehensive public health programs addressing priority health issues in Lideta Subcity, including immunization campaigns, maternal health initiatives, disease prevention programs, and health promotion activities","Conduct regular community health assessments through household surveys, health facility data analysis, and epidemiological investigations to identify health trends, risk factors, and emerging public health threats","Investigate and respond to disease outbreaks and public health emergencies by conducting field investigations, coordinating response teams, implementing control measures, and monitoring containment efforts","Develop and deliver culturally appropriate health education materials, workshops, and community outreach programs targeting diverse populations including schools, religious institutions, workplaces, and community organizations","Monitor and evaluate health service delivery at public and private health facilities within the subcity, assessing quality of care, service availability, and compliance with national health standards and protocols","Collect, analyze, and report public health data using standardized reporting systems, preparing comprehensive epidemiological reports, situation analyses, and program evaluations for government officials and stakeholders","Coordinate with regional health bureaus, NGOs, community-based organizations, and healthcare providers to align public health efforts, leverage resources, and implement integrated health interventions","Provide technical guidance and capacity building to community health workers, health extension workers, and volunteers on public health practices, data collection methods, and health education techniques"}','{"Bachelor of Science degree in Public Health, Health Sciences, Nursing, or related field from an accredited university with coursework in epidemiology, biostatistics, and community health","Minimum of three years of practical public health experience in community health programming, disease surveillance, health education, or related fields within government or NGO settings","Comprehensive knowledge of Ethiopian public health system, national health policies, primary healthcare strategy, and priority health programs with understanding of local health challenges in urban settings","Demonstrated experience in epidemiological investigation, data collection and analysis, outbreak response, and use of health information systems for monitoring and evaluation purposes","Excellent community engagement and health communication skills with ability to develop culturally appropriate health messages and deliver effective health education to diverse populations","Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with ability to interpret health data, identify trends, and develop evidence-based recommendations for public health interventions","Proficiency in data analysis software (EPI Info, SPSS, or similar) and Microsoft Office applications for data management, analysis, and report preparation","Ability to work independently and collaboratively in multidisciplinary teams, manage multiple projects simultaneously, and adapt to changing public health priorities and emergencies"}','{"epidemiology","community_engagement","data_analysis"}','2024-01-16','2024-02-16'),
        ('Environmental Inspector','Enforce environmental regulations and conduct facility inspections. Monitor compliance with air quality and waste management standards.','As an Environmental Inspector for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for enforcing environmental regulations, conducting comprehensive inspections of commercial and industrial facilities, and ensuring compliance with national and municipal environmental standards. Your role involves systematic evaluation of pollution sources, waste management practices, and environmental impact of various activities within the subcity. You will conduct detailed inspections of manufacturing facilities, service establishments, construction sites, and residential developments to assess compliance with air quality standards, water pollution controls, waste disposal regulations, and noise pollution limits. This position requires technical knowledge of environmental science, regulatory frameworks, and inspection methodologies. You will investigate environmental complaints from residents, recommend corrective actions, and follow up on violations to ensure proper remediation. Additionally, you will contribute to environmental policy development and public education initiatives aimed at promoting sustainable practices within the Lideta community.','Lideta Subcity',52000,'fulltime','Environment','{"Conduct scheduled and surprise inspections of industrial facilities, commercial establishments, construction sites, and service providers to assess compliance with environmental regulations, permits, and standards","Investigate environmental complaints from residents regarding pollution, improper waste disposal, noise violations, and other environmental concerns, documenting findings and recommending appropriate enforcement actions","Collect environmental samples (air, water, soil) following standardized protocols, coordinate laboratory analysis, interpret results, and prepare technical reports on environmental quality and pollution levels","Issue notices of violation, compliance orders, and administrative penalties to facilities failing to meet environmental standards, maintaining detailed records of enforcement actions and follow-up activities","Evaluate environmental impact assessments and management plans for proposed developments, providing technical recommendations and monitoring implementation of mitigation measures","Conduct environmental audits of facilities to assess overall environmental performance, identify improvement opportunities, and develop compliance schedules for corrective actions","Prepare comprehensive inspection reports with findings, observations, photographs, measurements, and recommendations for regulatory compliance and environmental protection","Provide technical guidance and education to business owners, facility managers, and community members on environmental regulations, pollution prevention techniques, and sustainable practices"}','{"Bachelor degree in Environmental Science, Environmental Engineering, Chemistry, or related field with specialized coursework in environmental regulations, pollution control, and environmental monitoring","Minimum of three years of professional experience in environmental inspection, compliance monitoring, pollution control, or regulatory enforcement within government or industrial settings","In-depth knowledge of Ethiopian environmental laws, regulations, standards, and permitting requirements at federal, regional, and municipal levels with understanding of enforcement procedures","Technical proficiency in environmental monitoring techniques, sampling protocols, field measurement equipment, and laboratory analysis methods for air, water, and soil quality parameters","Strong investigative and analytical skills with ability to interpret technical data, identify regulatory violations, and develop appropriate enforcement responses based on risk assessment","Excellent report writing and documentation skills with ability to prepare clear, comprehensive, and legally defensible inspection reports, violation notices, and compliance documentation","Effective communication and interpersonal skills with ability to explain complex environmental regulations to diverse audiences, negotiate compliance agreements, and handle confrontational situations professionally","Physical ability to conduct field inspections in various environments, including industrial facilities, construction sites, and potentially hazardous conditions, with appropriate safety precautions"}','{"regulatory_compliance","environmental_monitoring","technical_reporting"}','2024-01-17','2024-02-17'),
        ('IT Support Technician','Provide technical support for government computer systems and networks. Troubleshoot hardware/software issues and maintain IT infrastructure.','As an IT Support Technician for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will provide comprehensive technical support for all computer systems, networks, software applications, and peripheral devices used by government staff across multiple departments. Your responsibilities include installing, configuring, maintaining, and troubleshooting hardware and software systems to ensure optimal performance and minimal downtime. You will serve as the first point of contact for all IT-related issues, providing timely resolution to technical problems while maintaining detailed documentation of support requests and solutions. This position requires broad technical knowledge across multiple platforms and systems, with particular emphasis on government-specific applications and security protocols. You will also be responsible for managing user accounts, implementing security measures, conducting regular system maintenance, and providing basic training to staff on IT systems and applications. Additionally, you will assist in IT inventory management, procurement processes, and implementation of new technologies to improve government service delivery.','Lideta Subcity Office',48000,'fulltime','Technology','{"Provide first-level technical support to government staff for hardware, software, network, and peripheral device issues through help desk ticketing system, phone support, and in-person assistance","Install, configure, and maintain desktop computers, laptops, printers, scanners, and other IT equipment according to government standards and security requirements","Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues with operating systems (Windows), productivity software (Microsoft Office), specialized government applications, and network connectivity problems","Manage user accounts, permissions, and access controls in Active Directory and other directory services, ensuring proper security protocols and compliance with government IT policies","Perform regular system maintenance including software updates, security patches, antivirus updates, and system backups to ensure optimal performance and data protection","Maintain detailed inventory records of IT equipment, software licenses, and consumables, tracking deployment, maintenance history, and retirement of assets according to government procedures","Provide basic training and guidance to government staff on proper use of IT systems, software applications, security practices, and troubleshooting techniques for common issues","Document technical procedures, solutions, and configurations in knowledge base system to improve support efficiency and ensure consistency in troubleshooting approaches"}','{"Diploma or Certificate in Information Technology, Computer Science, or related field with coursework in computer hardware, networking, and system administration","Minimum of two years of hands-on experience in IT support, help desk operations, or technical assistance role in organizational setting with diverse user base","Strong technical knowledge of Microsoft Windows operating systems, Microsoft Office Suite, desktop hardware components, printer configurations, and basic networking concepts","Experience with Active Directory user management, group policies, file permissions, and basic server administration in Windows Server environment","Proficiency in troubleshooting methodologies with ability to diagnose and resolve hardware, software, and network issues systematically and efficiently","Knowledge of cybersecurity principles, antivirus software, malware removal techniques, and data protection practices relevant to government IT environment","Excellent customer service and communication skills with ability to explain technical concepts to non-technical users patiently and clearly in both Amharic and English","Strong organizational skills with ability to prioritize multiple support requests, document solutions thoroughly, and follow established procedures for IT asset management"}','{"technical_troubleshooting","user_support","system_maintenance"}','2024-01-18','2024-02-18'),
        ('Civil Engineer','Design and supervise municipal infrastructure projects. Ensure compliance with engineering standards and manage construction activities.','As a Civil Engineer for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for planning, designing, supervising, and managing municipal infrastructure projects that enhance community development and improve public services. Your role encompasses the entire project lifecycle from initial feasibility studies and conceptual design through construction supervision and final commissioning. You will work on diverse infrastructure projects including road improvements, drainage systems, water supply networks, public building construction, and urban development initiatives. This position requires strong technical expertise in civil engineering principles, project management capabilities, and knowledge of Ethiopian construction standards and regulations. You will coordinate with contractors, consultants, and government agencies to ensure projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to specified quality standards. Additionally, you will conduct site inspections, review technical submissions, prepare engineering drawings and specifications, and provide technical advice to government officials on infrastructure planning and development.','Lideta Engineering Office',72000,'fulltime','Infrastructure','{"Plan, design, and prepare detailed engineering drawings, specifications, and cost estimates for municipal infrastructure projects including roads, drainage systems, water supply networks, and public facilities using AutoCAD and engineering software","Supervise construction activities on-site to ensure compliance with engineering designs, specifications, quality standards, safety regulations, and environmental requirements","Conduct feasibility studies, site investigations, and technical assessments for proposed infrastructure projects, analyzing soil conditions, topographic features, and existing utilities","Review and approve contractor submissions including method statements, shop drawings, material samples, and quality control plans to ensure compliance with project requirements","Monitor project progress against schedules and budgets, preparing regular progress reports, identifying potential delays or cost overruns, and recommending corrective actions","Coordinate with utility companies, government agencies, contractors, and community stakeholders to facilitate project implementation, resolve conflicts, and minimize disruptions","Conduct quality control inspections and testing of construction materials, workmanship, and finished works according to Ethiopian standards and project specifications","Provide technical guidance and mentorship to junior engineers, engineering technicians, and site supervisors on engineering principles, construction methods, and project management practices"}','{"Bachelor of Science degree in Civil Engineering from accredited university with coursework in structural design, transportation engineering, water resources, and construction management","Professional engineering license from Ethiopian Ministry of Works and Urban Development or eligibility for licensure with demonstrated knowledge of Ethiopian engineering standards and codes","Minimum of four years of progressive civil engineering experience in infrastructure project design, construction supervision, or project management in government or consulting environment","Advanced proficiency in AutoCAD Civil 3D, engineering design software, and project management tools with ability to create detailed engineering drawings and technical specifications","Strong knowledge of Ethiopian construction standards, building codes, road design specifications, and environmental regulations applicable to municipal infrastructure projects","Proven project management skills with experience in planning, budgeting, scheduling, resource allocation, and risk management for engineering projects of varying scale and complexity","Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities with capacity to evaluate engineering challenges, develop innovative solutions, and make sound technical decisions under pressure","Effective communication and coordination skills with ability to liaise with multiple stakeholders, write comprehensive technical reports, and present engineering concepts to diverse audiences"}','{"project_management","structural_design","construction_supervision"}','2024-01-19','2024-02-19'),
       
        ('Education Coordinator','Support school development and coordinate educational programs. Facilitate teacher professional development and monitor educational quality.','As an Education Coordinator for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will play a pivotal role in enhancing educational quality, supporting school development, and implementing educational programs across public and private institutions within the subcity. Your responsibilities encompass monitoring educational standards, facilitating teacher professional development, coordinating educational initiatives, and serving as a liaison between schools and government education authorities. You will conduct regular school visits to assess teaching practices, learning environments, and administrative systems, providing constructive feedback and support for improvement. This position requires deep understanding of Ethiopian educational policies, curriculum frameworks, and pedagogical approaches, along with strong interpersonal skills to build collaborative relationships with school administrators, teachers, parents, and community organizations. You will also coordinate special education programs, extracurricular activities, and community engagement initiatives that complement formal education and address diverse learning needs within the Lideta community.','Lideta Education Office',56000,'fulltime','Education','{"Conduct regular monitoring visits to public and private schools within Lideta Subcity to assess educational quality, teaching practices, learning outcomes, and compliance with national education standards","Coordinate and facilitate professional development programs, workshops, and training sessions for teachers, school administrators, and education professionals on curriculum implementation, pedagogy, and assessment practices","Implement and monitor government education initiatives, special programs, and pilot projects in schools, ensuring proper execution, documentation, and evaluation of program effectiveness","Serve as primary liaison between Lideta Subcity Education Office, individual schools, regional education bureau, and Ministry of Education, facilitating communication, policy implementation, and resource allocation","Organize and conduct regular meetings with school principals, parent-teacher associations, and community representatives to discuss educational challenges, share best practices, and develop improvement plans","Collect, analyze, and report educational data on enrollment, attendance, completion rates, examination results, and resource allocation to inform decision-making and policy development","Provide technical support and guidance to schools in developing school improvement plans, implementing inclusive education practices, and addressing specific learning needs of diverse student populations","Coordinate extracurricular activities, educational competitions, community service projects, and special events that enhance student learning, engagement, and holistic development"}','{"Bachelor degree in Education, Educational Leadership, Curriculum Development, or related field with specialization in pedagogy, educational administration, or teacher education","Minimum of four years of experience in educational coordination, school supervision, teacher support, or educational program management within government or school system","Comprehensive knowledge of Ethiopian education policy, curriculum framework, assessment system, teacher professional standards, and school accreditation requirements","Demonstrated experience in teacher professional development, instructional coaching, classroom observation, and feedback techniques that improve teaching practices and student learning","Strong analytical skills with ability to interpret educational data, identify trends and patterns, and develop evidence-based recommendations for educational improvement","Excellent interpersonal and communication skills with ability to build collaborative relationships with diverse stakeholders including teachers, administrators, parents, and government officials","Experience in organizing and facilitating workshops, training sessions, and professional learning communities for educators with focus on practical application and sustainable impact","Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously, prioritize competing demands, and work effectively in team environment while meeting deadlines and achieving educational objectives"}','{"educational_leadership","program_coordination","teacher_development"}','2024-01-20','2024-02-20'),
        ('Security Guard','Maintain safety and security at government office facilities. Conduct patrols and control access to protect government assets.','As a Security Guard for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for maintaining safety, security, and order at government facilities, protecting assets, personnel, and visitors from potential threats. Your role involves vigilant monitoring of premises, controlling access to restricted areas, conducting patrols, and responding to security incidents according to established protocols. You will serve as the first line of defense in protecting government property, confidential information, and public resources from theft, vandalism, unauthorized access, and other security risks. This position requires physical fitness, alertness, professional conduct, and knowledge of security procedures specific to government operations. You will interact daily with government employees, officials, and the public, requiring diplomacy and firmness in enforcing security policies. Additionally, you will maintain security logs, incident reports, and surveillance records, and collaborate with local law enforcement when necessary to address security concerns and maintain public trust in government facilities.','Lideta Subcity Office',32000,'fulltime','Security','{"Control access to government facilities by verifying identification, screening visitors, issuing visitor badges, and monitoring entry/exit points according to established security protocols","Conduct regular patrols of buildings, grounds, parking areas, and perimeter fences to detect security vulnerabilities, unauthorized activities, safety hazards, or suspicious behavior","Monitor surveillance systems, alarm panels, and security equipment to identify potential security threats, respond to alarms, and maintain continuous security coverage of premises","Respond promptly to security incidents, emergencies, or disturbances by assessing situations, taking appropria