ical challenges innovatively, and ensure memorable participant experiences","Knowledge of local venue options, vendor networks, cultural protocols, and community dynamics in Addis Ababa with understanding of government event requirements and protocols","Proficiency in event management software, Microsoft Office applications, and basic graphic design tools for creating event materials, managing registrations, and preparing event documentation"}','{"logistical_planning","stakeholder_coordination","event_evaluation"}','2024-01-22','2024-02-22'),
        ('Revenue Collector','Collect municipal taxes and fees efficiently. Maintain accurate financial records and assist taxpayers with obligations.','As a Revenue Collector for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for the efficient collection of municipal taxes, fees, licenses, and other government revenues in accordance with established regulations and procedures. Your role involves direct interaction with taxpayers, businesses, and property owners to assess liabilities, process payments, issue receipts, and maintain accurate financial records. You will implement revenue collection strategies that maximize compliance while maintaining positive relationships with the community and ensuring transparency in government financial operations. This position requires strong numerical skills, integrity, and knowledge of municipal revenue systems, tax laws, and collection procedures. You will conduct field collections, follow up on arrears, maintain taxpayer records, and contribute to revenue forecasting and analysis. Additionally, you will provide information and assistance to taxpayers regarding their obligations, payment options, and available exemptions, while identifying potential revenue leakages and recommending improvements to collection processes and systems.','Lideta Revenue Office',46000,'fulltime','Administration','{"Collect municipal taxes, fees, licenses, and other government revenues from individuals, businesses, and organizations according to established schedules, rates, and procedures","Issue official receipts, payment confirmations, and tax certificates for all collections, ensuring accurate documentation and proper accounting of all transactions","Maintain detailed records of revenue collections, taxpayer accounts, arrears, exemptions, and adjustments using manual registers and computerized revenue management systems","Conduct field collections and follow-up activities for delinquent accounts, communicating with taxpayers, explaining obligations, and arranging payment plans when appropriate","Verify taxpayer information, assess liabilities, calculate amounts due, and apply appropriate rates, exemptions, and penalties according to municipal regulations and policies","Prepare daily collection reports, reconciliation statements, and bank deposit slips, ensuring accuracy of financial records and timely transfer of collected funds to designated accounts","Provide information and assistance to taxpayers regarding tax obligations, payment procedures, available exemptions, appeal processes, and other revenue-related inquiries","Identify potential revenue leakages, non-compliance patterns, and collection challenges, recommending improvements to collection processes, systems, and taxpayer education initiatives"}','{"Diploma in Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, or related field with coursework in taxation, financial management, and record-keeping principles","Minimum of two years of experience in revenue collection, cash handling, financial transactions, or accounting functions in government, banking, or commercial environment","Strong numerical and computational skills with accuracy in calculating amounts, processing payments, and maintaining financial records according to accounting standards","Knowledge of municipal revenue systems, tax laws, fee structures, and collection procedures specific to Addis Ababa city administration and Lideta Subcity regulations","Integrity and honesty with ability to handle cash responsibly, maintain confidentiality of financial information, and demonstrate ethical conduct in revenue collection activities","Excellent communication and customer service skills with ability to explain tax requirements clearly, address taxpayer concerns professionally, and maintain positive community relations","Proficiency in basic computer applications including spreadsheet software, revenue management systems, and digital payment processing tools used in government collections