        ('Sanitation Supervisor','Oversee waste collection and street cleaning services. Supervise sanitation workers and ensure service quality.','As a Sanitation Supervisor for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for overseeing waste collection, street cleaning, and sanitation services that maintain public health and environmental quality throughout the subcity. Your role involves direct supervision of sanitation workers, route planning, equipment maintenance, and quality assurance of cleaning operations. You will develop and implement efficient waste collection systems, monitor service delivery against established standards, and respond to community complaints regarding sanitation issues. This position requires practical knowledge of solid waste management principles, supervisory skills, and ability to coordinate operations across diverse urban neighborhoods. You will ensure compliance with municipal regulations, safety protocols, and environmental standards while optimizing resource utilization and service coverage. Additionally, you will conduct regular inspections of public areas, monitor contractor performance, maintain sanitation records, and develop improvement plans to address service gaps and enhance cleanliness standards in Lideta communities.','Lideta Sanitation Office',50000,'fulltime','Environment','{"Supervise daily sanitation operations including waste collection teams, street sweepers, and cleaning crews, ensuring proper performance of duties according to schedules and standards","Plan and optimize waste collection routes, service frequencies, and crew assignments to maximize efficiency, coverage, and responsiveness to community sanitation needs","Monitor equipment condition including collection vehicles, bins, hand tools, and personal protective equipment, scheduling maintenance, repairs, and replacements as needed","Conduct regular quality inspections of public areas, streets, markets, and communal spaces to assess cleanliness standards, identify problem areas, and direct corrective actions","Respond to and investigate sanitation complaints from residents, businesses, and community organizations, coordinating timely resolution and following up on service improvements","Maintain accurate records of sanitation operations including collection volumes, service coverage, equipment usage, personnel attendance, and incident reports for management review","Implement safety protocols and training programs for sanitation workers on proper lifting techniques, equipment operation, hazardous material handling, and personal protection measures","Coordinate with other municipal departments, private contractors, community organizations, and environmental agencies to address integrated waste management challenges and initiatives"}','{"Completion of secondary education with additional training in environmental management, waste management, public health, or supervisory skills from recognized institution","Minimum of three years of experience in sanitation operations, waste management, or environmental services with at least one year in supervisory or team leadership role","Practical knowledge of solid waste management principles, collection systems, equipment operation, and sanitation best practices in urban environment","Supervisory and leadership skills with ability to direct work teams, resolve conflicts, provide training, and maintain discipline among sanitation personnel","Familiarity with municipal sanitation regulations, environmental standards, safety requirements, and service quality expectations for public sanitation services","Physical ability to conduct field inspections, demonstrate work methods, and supervise operations in various weather conditions and urban environments","Problem-solving skills with capacity to analyze sanitation challenges, develop practical solutions, and implement improvements to service delivery systems","Valid driver license with ability to operate sanitation vehicles or supervise vehicle operations, and basic literacy in record-keeping and reporting requirements"}','{"waste_management","team_supervision","quality_inspection"}','2024-01-24','2024-02-24'),
        ('Social Worker','Provide social services to vulnerable individuals and families. Conduct assessments and coordinate support services.','As a Social Worker for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will provide comprehensive social services to vulnerable individuals and families, addressing psychosocial needs, facilitating access to resources, and promoting social inclusion within the community. Your role involves assessment, counseling, case management, and advocacy for diverse client populations including children at risk, persons with disabilities, elderly individuals, economically disadvantaged families, and other marginalized groups. You will conduct home visits, develop care plans, coordinate with service providers, and implement interventions that enhance wellbeing and resilience. This position requires deep understanding of social work principles, Ethiopian social protection systems, and community resources, along with strong empathy, cultural competence, and ethical practice. You will maintain confidential case records, prepare reports, participate in multidisciplinary teams, and contribute to policy development addressing social issues. Additionally, you will organize support groups, community awareness activities, and capacity-building initiatives that strengthen social networks and promote protective environments for vulnerable populations in Lideta.','Lideta Social Office',54000,'fulltime','Health','{"Conduct comprehensive psychosocial assessments of individuals and families referred for social services, identifying needs, strengths, risks, and appropriate intervention strategies","Provide professional counseling services addressing emotional, behavioral, relationship, and adjustment issues using evidence-based therapeutic approaches tailored to client circumstances","Develop and implement individualized care plans with clients, setting achievable goals, identifying resources, coordinating services, and monitoring progress toward improved wellbeing","Conduct regular home visits and community outreach to engage with vulnerable populations, assess living conditions, provide in-situ support, and connect clients with essential services","Maintain detailed case records, progress notes, assessment reports, and service documentation according to professional standards and government reporting requirements","Coordinate with healthcare providers, educational institutions, legal services, employment programs, and community organizations to create integrated support networks for clients","Facilitate support groups, parenting workshops, life skills training, and community awareness sessions addressing prevalent social issues and building protective factors","Advocate for client rights and needs within government systems, service networks, and community settings, addressing barriers to access and promoting inclusive policies and practices"}','{"Bachelor of Social Work degree from accredited institution with coursework in counseling, case management, human behavior, and social welfare policy","Professional registration with relevant Ethiopian social work association or eligibility for registration with demonstrated knowledge of ethical standards and practice guidelines","Minimum of three years of professional social work experience in community-based setting with diverse client populations and complex psychosocial needs","Comprehensive knowledge of Ethiopian social protection system, community resources, referral pathways, and legal frameworks relevant to vulnerable populations","Strong counseling and interviewing skills with ability to establish rapport, conduct sensitive assessments, provide therapeutic support, and maintain professional boundaries","Case management expertise including assessment, planning, implementation, coordination, monitoring, and evaluation of services for individuals and families","Cultural competence and sensitivity in working with diverse populations, understanding community dynamics, traditional support systems, and appropriate intervention approaches","Excellent documentation and reporting skills with ability to maintain confidential records, prepare case summaries, and contribute to program evaluation and policy development"}','{"counseling_skills","case_management","community_advocacy"}','2024-01-25','2024-02-25'),
        ('Building Inspector','Examine construction projects for code compliance. Conduct inspections and provide technical guidance to contractors.','As a Building Inspector for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for examining construction projects at various stages to ensure compliance with building codes, zoning regulations, approved plans, and safety standards. Your role involves conducting detailed inspections of structural elements, electrical systems, plumbing installations, fire safety measures, and accessibility features in new construction, renovations, and existing buildings. You will review construction documents, issue inspection reports, identify code violations, and approve work progression based on compliance with regulatory requirements. This position requires technical knowledge of building systems, construction methods, and Ethiopian building codes, along with strong observational skills and attention to detail. You will interact with architects, engineers, contractors, property owners, and other stakeholders, providing technical guidance and enforcement of construction regulations. Additionally, you will investigate building complaints, dangerous structures, and illegal constructions, recommending corrective actions and follow-up measures to ensure public safety and regulatory compliance throughout Lideta Subcity.','Lideta Planning Office',58000,'fulltime','Infrastructure','{"Conduct scheduled inspections at critical construction stages including foundation, framing, electrical, plumbing, mechanical, and final completion to verify compliance with approved plans and building codes","Review construction documents, architectural drawings, engineering calculations, and permit applications to understand project requirements and identify potential compliance issues","Issue inspection reports detailing findings, observations, measurements, photographs, and compliance status, specifying corrections needed for non-conforming work","