nical requirements clearly, document findings precisely, and interact professionally with diverse stakeholders in construction process","Physical ability to access construction sites, climb ladders, enter confined spaces, and conduct inspections in various weather conditions and construction environments"}','{"code_enforcement","construction_inspection","technical_documentation"}','2024-01-26','2024-02-26'),
        ('Records Clerk','Organize and maintain government documents and archives. Implement records management systems and process requests.','As a Records Clerk for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for the systematic organization, maintenance, retrieval, and preservation of government documents, files, and archival materials essential for administrative operations and public service delivery. Your role involves implementing records management systems, classifying documents, creating finding aids, and ensuring proper storage conditions for both physical and digital records. You will process document requests, assist staff in locating information, and maintain confidentiality of sensitive materials according to government regulations. This position requires meticulous attention to detail, organizational skills, and knowledge of records management principles specific to government operations. You will contribute to digitization initiatives, disaster recovery planning, and records retention schedule implementation. Additionally, you will provide training to staff on proper records handling procedures, monitor compliance with documentation standards, and develop improvements to information management systems that enhance efficiency and accessibility of government records.','Lideta Archives Office',38000,'fulltime','Administration','{"Classify, index, and catalog government documents, files, and records according to established classification systems, metadata standards, and retrieval requirements","Maintain organized filing systems for physical documents including correspondence, reports, applications, permits, and official records with proper labeling and storage arrangements","Process document requests from government staff, officials, and authorized external parties by locating, retrieving, copying, and recording circulation of requested materials","Implement records retention schedules by identifying records eligible for destruction, transferring archival materials to permanent storage, and documenting disposal activities","Assist in digitization projects by preparing documents for scanning, verifying digital copies against originals, and entering metadata for electronic records management","Maintain proper storage conditions for archival materials including temperature and humidity control, pest prevention, and appropriate handling procedures for fragile documents","Create finding aids, indexes, catalogs, and databases to facilitate efficient retrieval of information from both physical and digital records collections","Provide training and guidance to government staff on proper records creation, classification, handling, and disposition procedures according to established policies and standards"}','{"Completion of secondary education with additional training in records management, archival science, library science, or information management from recognized institution","Minimum of two years of experience in records management, filing operations, archival work, or library services in organizational setting","Knowledge of records management principles, classification systems, retention schedules, and preservation techniques for both paper and electronic records","Attention to detail and organizational skills with ability to maintain systematic order in document collections, follow precise procedures, and ensure accuracy in records handling","Familiarity with government document types, filing requirements, confidentiality protocols, and administrative procedures specific to Ethiopian government operations","Basic computer skills including proficiency in word processing, spreadsheet applications, database entry, and scanning equipment operation for records management tasks","Ability to work independently with minimal supervision while maintaining productivity, accuracy, and adherence to established records management protocols","Physical ability to handle boxes of documents, operate filing equipment, and