        ('Urban Planner','Develop urban planning initiatives for sustainable development. Analyze spatial data and review project compliance.','As an Urban Planner for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for developing, implementing, and monitoring urban planning initiatives that guide sustainable development, optimize land use, and enhance quality of life within the subcity. Your role involves analyzing spatial data, preparing development plans, reviewing projects for compliance, and engaging stakeholders in planning processes. You will work on comprehensive plans, zoning regulations, transportation networks, public space designs, and redevelopment projects that balance growth with environmental protection and community needs. This position requires technical expertise in urban planning principles, GIS applications, regulatory frameworks, and participatory planning methods. You will conduct site analyses, prepare maps and visualizations, evaluate development proposals, and provide recommendations to decision-makers. Additionally, you will facilitate public consultations, coordinate with other government agencies, conduct research on urban issues, and contribute to policy development addressing urbanization challenges and opportunities in Lideta Subcity.','Lideta Planning Office',68000,'fulltime','Infrastructure','{"Develop comprehensive urban plans, land use maps, zoning regulations, and development guidelines that promote sustainable growth, efficient infrastructure, and improved quality of life","Review and evaluate development proposals, construction permits, and land subdivision applications for compliance with urban planning regulations, standards, and community objectives","Conduct spatial analysis using GIS software to assess land suitability, development patterns, infrastructure capacity, environmental constraints, and demographic trends","Prepare planning documents, technical reports, policy recommendations, and visual presentations that communicate planning concepts, analysis findings, and implementation strategies","Facilitate public participation processes including community meetings, stakeholder workshops, focus groups, and consultation events to gather input on planning initiatives","Coordinate with other government departments, utility providers, transportation agencies, and environmental authorities to ensure integrated planning and implementation of projects","Monitor urban development trends, land use changes, and implementation of planning policies, preparing periodic evaluation reports and recommending adjustments as needed","Provide technical advice to government officials, developers, community organizations, and other stakeholders on urban planning matters, regulatory requirements, and development opportunities"}','{"Bachelor or Master degree in Urban Planning, Urban Studies, Geography, Architecture, or related field with specialization in spatial planning and development management","Professional certification or registration as urban planner with relevant Ethiopian professional association or eligibility for certification","Minimum of four years of professional urban planning experience in government, consulting, or development sector with portfolio of completed planning projects","Advanced proficiency in GIS software (ArcGIS, QGIS), spatial analysis techniques, mapping tools, and data visualization methods for urban planning applications","Strong knowledge of Ethiopian urban planning legislation, land use regulations, building codes, environmental laws, and municipal planning frameworks","Analytical and research skills with ability to collect, interpret, and synthesize diverse data sources including demographic statistics, economic indicators, and spatial information","Communication and facilitation skills with ability to engage diverse stakeholders, present technical information clearly, and build consensus on planning decisions","Project management capabilities including planning, budgeting, timeline development, team coordination, and monitoring of planning initiatives from conception to implementation"}','{"spatial_analysis","planning_regulations","stakeholder_engagement"}','2024-01-29','2024-02-29'),
        ('Health Educator','Develop health education programs for community health promotion. Design materials and conduct educational workshops.','As a Health Educator for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will develop and implement comprehensive health education programs that promote healthy behaviors, prevent diseases, and improve health literacy within diverse community populations. Your role involves assessing community health needs, designing culturally appropriate educational materials, conducting workshops and training sessions, and evaluating program effectiveness. You will address priority health issues including infectious diseases, maternal and child health, nutrition, sanitation, non-communicable diseases, and mental health through evidence-based educational strategies. This position requires expertise in health communication, behavioral change theories, and participatory education methods adapted to various audience characteristics and learning styles. You will collaborate with healthcare providers, community organizations, schools, and media outlets to disseminate health messages and create supportive environments for healthy choices. Additionally, you will train community health workers, develop health promotion campaigns, conduct research on health behaviors, and contribute to policy development addressing health education needs in Lideta communities.','Lideta Health Center',52000,'fulltime','Health','{"Assess community health education needs through surveys, focus groups, interviews, and data analysis to identify priority topics, knowledge gaps, and behavioral risk factors","Develop culturally appropriate health education materials, visual aids, curriculum modules, and communication tools addressing identified health issues for diverse population groups","Design and implement health education programs, workshops, training sessions, and community events using participatory methods that engage learners and promote behavioral change","Conduct educational sessions in various community settings including schools, workplaces, religious institutions, community centers, and healthcare facilities","Evaluate health education interventions through pre/post assessments, participant feedback, behavioral monitoring, and outcome measurement to determine effectiveness and identify improvements","Train and support community health workers, volunteers, peer educators, and other stakeholders in health education techniques, message delivery, and facilitation skills","Develop and implement health promotion campaigns using multiple communication channels including print media, radio, social media, community radio, and interpersonal communication","Collaborate with healthcare providers, government agencies, NGOs, and community organizations to integrate health education into broader health initiatives and service delivery systems"}','{"Bachelor degree in Health Education, Public Health, Nursing, Health Sciences, or related field with coursework in health communication and behavioral change theories","Minimum of three years of professional experience in health education, health promotion, community health, or related field with demonstrated program development skills","Knowledge of Ethiopian health priorities, prevalent health issues, traditional health beliefs, and cultural factors influencing health behaviors in urban communities","Expertise in health communication strategies, educational methodologies, adult learning principles, and participatory techniques for diverse audience groups","Creative skills in developing health education materials, visual aids, interactive tools, and multimedia resources that effectively convey health messages and information","Facilitation and presentation skills with ability to engage audiences, adapt delivery to different learning styles, and create supportive learning environments","Evaluation and research skills with ability to assess educational needs, measure learning outcomes, analyze behavioral data, and report program effectiveness","Cultural competence and sensitivity in working with diverse communities, understanding social determinants of health, and adapting approaches to local contexts"}','{"health_communication","program_development","community_facilitation"}','2024-01-30','2024-02-28'),
        ('IT Systems Administrator','Design and maintain government network infrastructure. Ensure system reliability, performance, and security.','As an IT Systems Administrator for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for designing, implementing, maintaining, and securing the government network infrastructure, server systems, and IT services that support administrative operations and public service delivery. Your role encompasses system installation, configuration, monitoring, troubleshooting, and optimization to ensure reliability, performance, and security of critical IT assets. You will manage Windows Server environments, Active Directory services, email systems, backup solutions, and network equipment while implementing security measures to protect sensitive government data. This position requires advanced technical skills, problem-solving abilities, and knowledge of government IT requirements and security standards. You will develop system documentation, disaster recovery plans, and performance monitoring procedures, while providing technical leadership to IT support staff. Additionally, you will evaluate new technologies, plan system upgrades, coordinate with external service providers, and ensure compliance with government IT policies and cybersecurity regulations.','Lideta IT Office',65000,'fulltime','Technology','{"Administer and maintain Windows Server environments including Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, Group Policy, file services, print services, and authentication systems","Design, implement, and secure government network infrastructure including routers, switches, firewalls, wireless access points, VPN connections, and internet connectivity","Monitor system performance, capacity, and security using management tools, analyzing trends, identifying issues, and implementing optimizations to maintain service levels","Implement and manage backup and disaster recovery solutions including regular backups, recovery testing, offsite storage, and business continuity planning","Configure and maintain email systems, collaboration platforms, antivirus solutions, patch management systems, and other enterprise applications used in government operations","Implement security measures including firewall rules, intrusion detection, access controls, encryption, security policies, and vulnerability management to protect government systems","Provide technical support escalation for complex IT issues, troubleshooting system failures, performance problems, and security incidents with systematic problem-solving approach","Develop and maintain system documentation, configuration records, network diagrams, operational procedures, and knowledge base articles for IT systems and infrastructure"}','{"Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Network Engineering, or related field with coursework in system administration and network security","Professional certifications in system administration (MCSA, MCSE) or networking (CCNA, Network+) with demonstrated technical expertise in enterprise IT environments","Minimum of four years of hands-on experience in system administration, network management, or IT infrastructure role in organizational setting","Advanced knowledge of Windows Server administration, Active Directory management, Group Policy implementation, and Microsoft enterprise services","Network administration skills including TCP/IP networking, routing protocols, VLAN configuration, firewall management, and wireless network implementation","Security expertise including security hardening, intrusion prevention, access control, encryption technologies, and compliance with government security standards","Problem-solving and troubleshooting abilities with systematic approach to diagnosing complex technical issues across multiple systems and network layers","Documentation and planning skills with ability to develop system documentation, operational procedures, disaster recovery plans, and technology roadmaps"}','{"system_administration","network_security","infrastructure_management"}','2024-02-01','2024-03-01'),
        ('Traffic Officer','Manage traffic flow and enforce regulations. Investigate accidents and promote road safety.','As a Traffic Officer for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for managing traffic flow, enforcing traffic regulations, investigating accidents, and promoting road safety within the subcity jurisdiction. Your role involves directing traffic at congested intersections, monitoring compliance with traffic laws, issuing citations for violations, and responding to traffic incidents and emergencies. You will work to reduce traffic congestion, prevent accidents, and ensure orderly movement of vehicles and pedestrians through systematic enforcement and public education. This position requires knowledge of traffic regulations, enforcement procedures, accident investigation techniques, and public safety principles. You will interact daily with drivers, pedestrians, business owners, and community members, requiring diplomacy, firmness, and professionalism in potentially stressful situations. Additionally, you will collect traffic data, prepare incident reports, participate in safety campaigns, and collaborate with other law enforcement agencies to address traffic challenges and improve road safety outcomes in Lideta communities.','Lideta Traffic Office',44000,'fulltime','Security','{"Direct and control traffic flow at congested intersections, school zones, construction areas, and special events using hand signals, whistle commands, and traffic control devices","Enforce traffic regulations by monitoring vehicle operations, identifying violations, stopping offending vehicles, checking documentation, and issuing citations or warnings as appropriate","Investigate traffic accidents by securing scenes, documenting evidence, measuring skid marks, interviewing witnesses, preparing diagrams, and determining contributing factors","Respond to traffic emergencies, incidents, and obstructions by implementing temporary traffic controls, rerouting vehicles, coordinating with emergency services, and clearing hazards","Monitor parking regulations by patrolling designated areas, identifying violations, issuing parking citations, and arranging for vehicle removal when necessary","Collect traffic data through manual counts, speed measurements, congestion observations, and violation patterns to inform traffic management decisions and enforcement priorities","Provide public education on traffic safety through interactions with drivers and pedestrians, distribution of educational materials, and participation in community safety campaigns","Prepare detailed incident reports, violation records, daily activity logs, and statistical summaries documenting traffic enforcement activities, observations, and outcomes"}','{"Completion of secondary education with specialized traffic police training from recognized police academy or traffic enforcement training institution","Minimum of three years of experience in traffic management, law enforcement, or public safety role with demonstrated knowledge of traffic regulations and enforcement procedures","Physical fitness and stamina to stand for extended periods, direct traffic in various weather conditions, and perform traffic control duties in potentially hazardous environments","Knowledge of Ethiopian traffic laws, vehicle codes, enforcement procedures, accident investigation techniques, and traffic control methods","Observational and decision-making skills with ability to assess traffic situations quickly, identify violations accurately, and take appropriate enforcement actions","Communication and interpersonal skills with ability to interact professionally with diverse individuals, explain violations clearly, and maintain composure in confrontational situations","Basic report writing and documentation skills with ability to complete incident reports, violation forms, and activity logs accurately and legibly","Valid driver license with clean driving record and ability to operate traffic enforcement vehicles or motorcycles as required for patrol duties"}','{"traffic_control","enforcement_procedures","accident_investigation"}','2024-02-02','2024-03-02'),
        ('Community Development Officer','Coordinate community development initiatives and projects. Facilitate participatory planning and build capacity.','As a Community Development Officer for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will coordinate and implement community development initiatives that address local needs, build community capacity, and enhance quality of life through participatory planning and project management. Your role involves identifying community priorities, mobilizing resources, facilitating partnerships, and managing development projects that deliver tangible benefits to residents. You will work with community organizations, neighborhood associations, local leaders, and government agencies to design and implement projects addressing infrastructure, social services, economic opportunities, and environmental improvements. This position requires understanding of community development principles, participatory methodologies, project management, and local governance structures. You will conduct community assessments, facilitate planning processes, prepare project proposals, monitor implementation, and evaluate outcomes. Additionally, you will build community leadership, strengthen social cohesion, promote citizen participation in governance, and document best practices for replication and scaling of successful development approaches in Lideta neighborhoods.','Lideta Development Office',59000,'fulltime','Administration','{"Conduct community needs assessments through participatory methods including surveys, focus groups, community meetings, and resource mapping to identify development priorities","Facilitate community planning processes that engage residents in identifying problems, developing solutions, prioritizing actions, and creating community development plans","Develop project proposals, funding applications, and implementation plans for community development initiatives addressing identified needs and priorities","Mobilize and coordinate community resources, volunteer contributions, local expertise, and in-kind support for development projects to maximize impact and sustainability","Manage implementation of community development projects including activity planning, budget monitoring, progress tracking, quality assurance, and reporting to stakeholders","Build capacity of community organizations, neighborhood associations, and local leaders through training, mentoring, and technical support on organizational development and project management","Facilitate partnerships and collaboration between community groups, government agencies, NGOs, private sector, and academic institutions to leverage resources and expertise","Monitor and evaluate community development initiatives through participatory evaluation methods, outcome measurement, impact assessment, and documentation of lessons learned"}','{"Bachelor degree in Community Development, Social Work, Development Studies, Sociology, or related field with coursework in participatory development and project management","Minimum of four years of professional experience in community development, participatory planning, project management, or community organizing in urban setting","Knowledge of community development principles, participatory methodologies, asset-based approaches, and sustainable development practices applicable to urban communities","Project management skills including planning, implementation, monitoring, evaluation, budgeting, and reporting for community-based development initiatives","Facilitation and training skills with ability to engage diverse community groups, build consensus, manage conflicts, and build local capacity through participatory processes","Community mobilization and organizing abilities with experience in working with community organizations, neighborhood associations, and local governance structures","Communication and relationship-building skills with ability to work effectively with diverse stakeholders including residents, leaders, officials, and partner organizations","Analytical and documentation skills with ability to assess community needs, evaluate project outcomes, document best practices, and prepare comprehensive development reports"}','{"participatory_planning","project_management","community_mobilization"}','2024-02-03','2024-03-03'),
        ('Part-time Cleaner','Maintain cleanliness of government office facilities. Perform cleaning tasks and ensure sanitary work environments.','As a Part-time Cleaner for Lideta Subcity Government Office, you will be responsible for maintaining cleanliness, hygiene, and orderly appearance of government office facilities through systematic cleaning procedures and attention to detail. Your role involves performing cleaning tasks in offices, meeting rooms, corridors, restrooms, and common areas according to established schedules and standards. You will ensure that work environments are sanitary, safe, and presentable for government staff, officials, and visitors, contributing to professional image and healthy working conditions. This position requires reliability, thoroughness, and understanding of proper cleaning techniques, equipment operation, and chemical safety. You will work independently with minimal supervision, managing time effectively to complete assigned tasks within designated hours while maintaining quality standards. Additionally, you will monitor cleaning supplies, report maintenance needs, follow safety protocols, and adapt cleaning routines to address specific needs or special events within government facilities.','Lideta Subcity Office',18000,'parttime','Environment','{"Perform daily cleaning of assigned office areas including dusting furniture, wiping surfaces, emptying trash bins, vacuuming carpets, and mopping hard floor surfaces","Clean and sanitize restroom facilities including toilets, urinals, sinks, mirrors, fixtures, and floors, replenishing supplies such as toilet paper, soap, and paper towels","Clean windows, glass doors, and transparent partitions using appropriate cleaning solutions and techniques to maintain clear visibility and professional appearance","Clean kitchen and break room areas including countertops, appliances, sinks, and cabinets, ensuring hygienic conditions for food preparation and consumption","Perform periodic deep cleaning tasks including carpet shampooing, floor stripping and waxing, wall washing, and detailed cleaning of light fixtures and vents","Operate and maintain cleaning equipment including vacuum cleaners, floor buffers, carpet extractors, and other tools, performing basic maintenance and reporting malfunctions","Monitor and replenish cleaning supplies, notifying supervisor when inventory is low and assisting with stock organization and storage","Follow safety protocols for chemical handling, equipment operation, and personal protection, using appropriate protective gear and storing cleaning materials securely"}','{"Basic literacy and numeracy skills with ability to follow written and verbal instructions, complete simple forms, and understand cleaning schedules and procedures","Previous cleaning experience in office, commercial, or institutional setting with demonstrated knowledge of cleaning techniques, equipment operation, and chemical safety","Physical ability to perform cleaning tasks including standing, bending, lifting, pushing, and carrying cleaning equipment and supplies throughout work shift","Reliability and punctuality with consistent attendance, ability to work independently with minimal supervision, and commitment to completing assigned tasks thoroughly","Attention to detail with ability to identify areas needing cleaning, maintain consistent quality standards, and ensure comprehensive coverage of assigned areas","Basic understanding of cleaning chemical properties, dilution ratios, application methods, and safety precautions to ensure effective and safe cleaning practices","Ability to work flexible hours including early mornings, evenings, or weekends as required by cleaning schedules or special events at government facilities","Positive attitude and professional demeanor with respect for government property, consideration for office occupants, and discretion in handling confidential observations"}','{"sanitary_cleaning","equipment_operation","attention_to_detail"}','2024-02-04','2024-02-20');


